# ==============================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# ==============================================

# KEEP TRACKING (use .gitkeep files to track empty directories)
# - data/           # Contains sensitive PDFs and passwords
# - reports/        # Contains generated Excel reports
# - logs/          # Contains log files with transaction data
# - coverage/      # Contains test coverage reports
# - examples/      # Keep directory structure
# - docs/          # Keep directory structure
# - scripts/       # Keep directory structure

# Any file containing sensitive data (passwords,
# API keys, bank statements, personal information)
# should NOT be committed to version control.
#
# If you accidentally commit sensitive data:
# 1. Remove the file immediately
# 2. Use git filter-branch or BFG to rewrite history
# 3. Force push to remote
# 4. Rotate all affected credentials